### @Component Decorator

Every Angular component is a class decorated with `@Component`. The decorator provides metadata that tells Angular how to create and use the component.

```typescript
import { Component } from '@angular/core';

@Component({
  selector: 'app-user-profile',
  templateUrl: './user-profile.component.html',
  styleUrls: ['./user-profile.component.css']
})
export class UserProfileComponent {
  username = 'john_doe';
}
```

### Key Metadata Properties

- **`selector`** — The CSS selector that identifies this component in a template. Common formats: `'app-user-profile'` (element), `'[app-user-profile]'` (attribute), `'.app-user-profile'` (class).
- **`templateUrl` / `template`** — External templateUrl or inline template string. Inline templates use backticks for multi-line.
- **`styleUrls` / `styles`** — External stylesheet array or inline styles array.
- **`standalone`** — When `true`, the component does not belong to an NgModule (Angular 14+).

### Inline Template Example

```typescript
@Component({
  selector: 'app-inline',
  template: `
    <div class="card">
      <h2>{{ title }}</h2>
      <p>{{ description }}</p>
    </div>
  `,
  styles: [`
    .card { border: 1px solid #ccc; padding: 1rem; }
    h2 { color: #333; }
  `]
})
export class InlineComponent {
  title = 'Hello';
  description = 'Inline template example';
}
```

### Component Tree

Angular applications form a **hierarchical component tree** rooted at `AppComponent`. Parent components nest child components via their selectors in the template:

```html
<!-- app.component.html -->
<app-header></app-header>
<app-sidebar></app-sidebar>
<main>
  <app-content></app-content>
</main>
<app-footer></app-footer>
```

Data flows down the tree via property bindings and events bubble up. Angular's change detection traverses this tree to update the DOM when data changes.

codeExample:
import { Component } from '@angular/core';

@Component({
  selector: 'app-greeting',
  template: `<h1>Hello, {{ name }}!</h1>`,
  styles: [`h1 { color: blue; }`],
  standalone: true
})
export class GreetingComponent {
  name = 'World';
}
